                "localizedMetadata": [
                    {
                        "description": "\nThis cohort provides distinct learning paths tailored to multiple roles that use Adobe Workfront Workflow:\n\nProject Managers: Learn to create and manage project timelines, how to collaborate effectively through the project, and monitor ongoing project work with Adobe Workfront. Follow a basic workflow that starts with reviewing a work request before creating and planning a project to manage related work. After launching the project, look at work progress indicators and how to troubleshoot situations that may arise. Finally, ensure all work is complete before closing the project.\nSystem Administrators",
                        "locale": "en-US",
                        "name": "Adobe Workfront Workflow Learning Cohort",
                        "overview": "Join a six-week guided learning experience designed to help you master the essentials of Adobe Workfront Workflow through live sessions, hands-on labs, and peer collaboration. Explore how other organizations are using Workfront with guest speakers and thought leadership sessions. Capstone projects prepare you to confidently use Adobe Workfront as a project manager or system administrator",
                        "richTextOverview": "<p>Join a six-week guided learning experience designed to help you master the essentials of Adobe Workfront Workflow through live sessions, hands-on labs, and peer collaboration. Explore how other organizations are using Workfront with guest speakers and thought leadership sessions. Capstone projects prepare you to confidently use Adobe Workfront as a project manager or system administrator<\/p>"
